title: Alex Goodman
text:
Welcome to my website! I am a statistics student at Cal Poly SLO. I enjoy statistics and working with data, and I am on a path forward towards a great career. My hobbies include running, travel, guitar, and reading.
Skills/Relevant coursework: SAS, JMP, R, Python, Tableau, Excel, Word, Statistical Computing in R, Statistical Computing in SAS, Linear Algebra, Methods of Proof, Probability Theory, Calculus I-IV, Applied Linear Models, Multilevel and Mixed Modeling, Survey Sampling and Methodology.

title: Projects
text:
A few of my projects are showcased below.
Data Visualization Project for Class: World’s Tallest Ferris Wheels, Pre-2018 -This was a project I worked on for a class to get my first experience with data visualization with Tableau, and I chose to work with Ferris Wheels. 
Ferris Wheel Dashboard
Data Visualization Self Project: Most Valuable Comic Books -This was a self project I decided to work on over the summer in Tableau, detailing the most expensive comics of every year sold for the most money. 
Comic Book Dashboard
Multilevel Modeling Report: NBA Draft Picks -This was a project for my multilevel and mixed regression modeling class, in which I helped investigate if NBA players picked earlier in the draft tend to have more game time on average than later drafts, in tandem with other factors.
Multilevel NBA Project
Data Analysis: Muffin Bake Heights -This was a project for a statistics course in which I collected data on 48 muffins, to see whether the level of oven rack (bottom or top) had a significant impact on a muffin’s overall baking height.
Muffin Project
